<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08004</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REQUIRING THE ESTABLISHMENT OF COMPUTER LABORATORY IN ALL PUBLIC ELEMENTARY AND SECONDARY SCHOOLS AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Recognizes the value of computer technology and access to the Internet in enhancing and facilitating learning and education of students in basic education.
Provides that every public elementary and high school shall have at least one room that shall be used as a computer laboratory and mandates DepEd to include in the curriculum of said schools, computer and internet literacy.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Computer and Internet Literacy for Public School Act”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NIETO, JOHN MARVIN &quot;YUL SERVO&quot; C., MACEDA, EDWARD VERA PEREZ, MARTINEZ, ERIC M., SANDOVAL, FEDERICO &quot;RICKY&quot; II S., MALAPITAN, DALE &quot;ALONG&quot; R.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Del Mar (000 2018-08-15)</td><td>2. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-09-06)</td><tr><td>3. Bravo (M.) (000 2018-11-19)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON BASIC EDUCATION AND CULTURE ON 2018-08-08</td></tr></table>